│ stop({"edit_points": [[17799, 17807, "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp"]], "thoughts": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash occurs in         │
│ SLPVectorizer during computeMinimumValueSizes -> collectValuesToDemote when checking if arithmetic shift right (AShr) operations can be demoted to smaller bit  │
│ widths. The failure is an assertion in llvm::cast<Instruction>(Value*), meaning the code tries to cast a Value to Instruction when it isn't one (e.g.,          │
│ PoisonValue or Constant), violating assumptions.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe debug log shows SLP processing bundles including PHIs and shifts, and          │
│ explicitly mentions encountering poison values (e.g., %c.4 has poison incoming). The backtrace pinpoints the crash at SLPVectorizer.cpp:17802 inside the        │
│ AShrChecker lambda of collectValuesToDemote. Other similar checkers (ShlChecker, LShrChecker) guard against PoisonValue by early returning true for poison      │
│ scalars; AShrChecker lacks this guard.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nIn collectValuesToDemote, for AShr, the code uses:\n  auto *I =                              │
│ cast<Instruction>(V);\nwithout verifying V is an Instruction. If any scalar in the tree entry is PoisonValue (or potentially a Constant), cast<Instruction>     │
│ asserts. This is consistent with the IR having PHIs that can carry poison values and with SLP gathering PHIs and reusing scalars. Shl/LShr checkers properly    │
│ handle PoisonValue via isa<PoisonValue>(V) checks; AShrChecker missed this, causing the invalid cast and abort.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Points(s):\nEdit the        │
│ AShrChecker in collectValuesToDemote to mirror SHL/LShr handling by checking for PoisonValue before casting.\n\nEdit Point:\nFile:                              │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\nLines: 17799-17807\nChange AShrChecker to:\n    auto AShrChecker = [&](unsigned BitWidth, unsigned             │
│ OrigBitWidth) {\n      return all_of(E.Scalars, [&](Value *V) {\n        if (isa<PoisonValue>(V))\n          return true;\n        auto *I =                    │
│ cast<Instruction>(V);\n        KnownBits AmtKnownBits = computeKnownBits(I->getOperand(1), *DL);\n        unsigned ShiftedBits = OrigBitWidth - BitWidth;\n     │
│ return AmtKnownBits.getMaxValue().ult(BitWidth) &&\n               ShiftedBits < ComputeNumSignBits(I->getOperand(0), *DL, 0, AC,\n                             │
│ nullptr, DT);\n      });\n    };\n\nReasoning:\n- Aligns AShrChecker with ShlChecker and LShrChecker which already handle PoisonValue.\n- Prevents              │
│ cast<Instruction> on non-instruction values.\n- Semantically correct: a poison lane doesn't prevent demotion as it can be considered trivially                  │
│ safe.\n\nOptional Consideration:\nIf other checkers (e.g., UDiv/URem, Call min/max/abs) similarly cast without a poison check, they may also need guards. The   │
│ backtrace shows the crash specifically within AShrChecker; the proposed fix addresses the immediate issue.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nThe crash is due to missing       │
