│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                                                                                                 │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                                                                                                     │
│ The crash occurs in SLPVectorizer during computeMinimumValueSizes -> collectValuesToDemote when checking if arithmetic shift right (AShr) operations can be     │
│ demoted to smaller bit widths. The failure is an assertion in llvm::cast<Instruction>(Value*), meaning the code tries to cast a Value to Instruction when it    │
│ isn't one (e.g., PoisonValue or Constant), violating assumptions.                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                                                                                                         │
│ The debug log shows SLP processing bundles including PHIs and shifts, and explicitly mentions encountering poison values (e.g., %c.4 has poison incoming). The  │
│ backtrace pinpoints the crash at SLPVectorizer.cpp:17802 inside the AShrChecker lambda of collectValuesToDemote. Other similar checkers (ShlChecker,            │
│ LShrChecker) guard against PoisonValue by early returning true for poison scalars; AShrChecker lacks this guard.                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                                                                                                         │
│ In collectValuesToDemote, for AShr, the code uses:                                                                                                              │
│   auto *I = cast<Instruction>(V);                                                                                                                               │
│ without verifying V is an Instruction. If any scalar in the tree entry is PoisonValue (or potentially a Constant), cast<Instruction> asserts. This is           │
│ consistent with the IR having PHIs that can carry poison values and with SLP gathering PHIs and reusing scalars. Shl/LShr checkers properly handle PoisonValue  │
│ via isa<PoisonValue>(V) checks; AShrChecker missed this, causing the invalid cast and abort.                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Points(s):                                                                                                                                     │
│ Edit the AShrChecker in collectValuesToDemote to mirror SHL/LShr handling by checking for PoisonValue before casting.                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ Edit Point:                                                                                                                                                     │
│ File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                                                                           │
│ Lines: 17799-17807                                                                                                                                              │
│ Change AShrChecker to:                                                                                                                                          │
│     auto AShrChecker = [&](unsigned BitWidth, unsigned OrigBitWidth) {                                                                                          │
│       return all_of(E.Scalars, [&](Value *V) {                                                                                                                  │
│         if (isa<PoisonValue>(V))                                                                                                                                │
│           return true;                                                                                                                                          │
│         auto *I = cast<Instruction>(V);                                                                                                                         │
│         KnownBits AmtKnownBits = computeKnownBits(I->getOperand(1), *DL);                                                                                       │
│         unsigned ShiftedBits = OrigBitWidth - BitWidth;                                                                                                         │
│         return AmtKnownBits.getMaxValue().ult(BitWidth) &&                                                                                                      │
│                ShiftedBits < ComputeNumSignBits(I->getOperand(0), *DL, 0, AC,                                                                                   │
│                                                 nullptr, DT);                                                                                                   │
│       });                                                                                                                                                       │
│     };                                                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ Reasoning:                                                                                                                                                      │
│ - Aligns AShrChecker with ShlChecker and LShrChecker which already handle PoisonValue.                                                                          │
│ - Prevents cast<Instruction> on non-instruction values.                                                                                                         │
│ - Semantically correct: a poison lane doesn't prevent demotion as it can be considered trivially safe.                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ Optional Consideration:                                                                                                                                         │
│ If other checkers (e.g., UDiv/URem, Call min/max/abs) similarly cast without a poison check, they may also need guards. The backtrace shows the crash           │
│ specifically within AShrChecker; the proposed fix addresses the immediate issue.                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                                                                                                  │
│ The crash is due to missing PoisonValue handling in AShrChecker causing an invalid cast to Instruction. Adding an early poison check prevents the assertion,    │
│ allowing SLP to safely continue demotion analysis. This fix mirrors existing patterns in nearby code and should resolve the reported reproducer.                │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                                                                                                 │
