  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash occurs in SLPVectorizer during computeMinimumValueSizes -> collectValuesToDemote when checking if
arithmetic shift right (AShr) operations can be demoted to smaller bit widths. The failure is an assertion in llvm::cast<Instruction>(Value*), meaning the code
tries to cast a Value to Instruction when it isn't one (e.g., PoisonValue or Constant), violating assumptions.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe debug log shows SLP
processing bundles including PHIs and shifts, and explicitly mentions encountering poison values (e.g., %c.4 has poison incoming). The backtrace pinpoints the
crash at SLPVectorizer.cpp:17802 inside the AShrChecker lambda of collectValuesToDemote. Other similar checkers (ShlChecker, LShrChecker) guard against PoisonValue
by early returning true for poison scalars; AShrChecker lacks this guard.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nIn collectValuesToDemote, for AShr, the code uses:\n  auto *I
= cast<Instruction>(V);\nwithout verifying V is an Instruction. If any scalar in the tree entry is PoisonValue (or potentially a Constant), cast<Instruction>
asserts. This is consistent with the IR having PHIs that can carry poison values and with SLP gathering PHIs and reusing scalars. Shl/LShr checkers properly handle
PoisonValue via isa<PoisonValue>(V) checks; AShrChecker missed this, causing the invalid cast and abort.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Points(s):\nEdit the AShrChecker in
collectValuesToDemote to mirror SHL/LShr handling by checking for PoisonValue before casting.\n\nEdit Point:\nFile:
llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\nLines: 17799-17807\nChange AShrChecker to:\n    auto AShrChecker = [&](unsigned BitWidth, unsigned OrigBitWidth)
